From: Keel <ci@keel.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH 0004/0006] keel: ui: 28px peek strip + summoned single-row toolbar

Adds Keel's two-state top bar:

  - Steady state: a 28-px translucent "peek" strip showing the active
    tab's favicon, host, and truncated title. Traffic-light area is
    drawn by us on every platform (native title bar replaced) so the
    look is consistent.

  - Summoned state: a single combined row containing window controls,
    nav buttons, the tab strip, the omnibox, extensions, and the menu.
    Slides down on cursor-proximity (top 60 px for ≥ 80 ms), F6,
    Ctrl+L, Ctrl+T, or any extension popup. Dismisses after the cursor
    leaves AND the page is focused AND 1200 ms elapsed.

Two new files, three small surgical edits to BrowserView. No changes to
input routing, drag-and-drop, accessibility tree, focus traversal, or
the compositor. The hotzone is a plain transparent View that listens
for OnMouseEntered/Exited via the existing event sink — same path the
omnibox uses for hover-style state.

Constants come from theme/tokens.json (topbar.* group). Animation uses
gfx::Tween::EASE_OUT at 180ms; respects ui::PrefersReducedMotion() →
instant.

Touches: chrome/browser/ui/views/ ONLY. No third_party/, no V8, no
network/, no media/, no sandbox/, no extensions permission code.

